<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="32" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="33.[192,1440,537,754]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,335,537,561]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Regarding the species of this group, we noted that 
<taxonomicName authority="Cadena-Castaneda and Cardona-Granda, 2015" authorityName="Cadena-Castaneda and Cardona-Granda" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Metrodora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis box="[953,1200,537,561]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Metrodora undulata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; J. M. Cardona-Granda" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" refId="ref13800" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J., and J. M. Cardona-Granda. 2015. Introduccion a los saltamontes de Colombia (Orthoptera: Caelifera, Acridomorpha, Tetrigoidea and Tridactyloidea). Lulu. com; Raleigh, NC. 534 p." type="book" year="2015">Cadena-Castañeda and Cardona-Granda, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[614,733,570,594]" name="Colombia" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, is not a member of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bolivar, 1887" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[991,1296,569,594]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Metrodora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[991,1119,569,593]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Metrodora</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bolivar, I." box="[1128,1296,570,594]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" pagination="175 - 313" refId="ref13750" refString="Bolivar, I. 1887. Essai sur les acridiens de la tribu des Tettigidae. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique 31: 175 - 313." type="journal article" year="1887">Bolívar, 1887</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but in fact represents a species of 
<emphasis box="[490,555,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar. In" authorityYear="1887" box="[490,551,602,625]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Cota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cota</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[624,728,602,626]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cadena-Castaneda and Cardona-Granda" authorityYear="2015" box="[773,931,601,625]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Metrodora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis box="[773,798,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[817,931,601,625]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">undulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has head and pronotal morphology corresponding to members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar. In" authorityYear="1887" box="[526,583,634,657]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Cota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[526,583,634,657]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Cota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, the new combination 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cadena-Castaneda and Cardona-Granda, 2015)" authorityName="Silva &amp; Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Pereira &amp; Domenico &amp; Sperber" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Cadena-Castaneda and Cardona-Granda" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Cota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undulata" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[951,1132,633,657]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Cota undulata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; J. M. Cardona-Granda" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" refId="ref13800" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J., and J. M. Cardona-Granda. 2015. Introduccion a los saltamontes de Colombia (Orthoptera: Caelifera, Acridomorpha, Tetrigoidea and Tridactyloidea). Lulu. com; Raleigh, NC. 534 p." type="book" year="2015">Cadena-Castañeda and Cardona-Granda, 2015</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[491,606,666,690]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[491,606,666,690]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
should be used when referring to this species. It is morphologically very close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[348,461,698,721]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Cota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saxosa">
<emphasis box="[348,461,698,721]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">C. saxosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[841,954,698,721]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Cota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saxosa">
<emphasis box="[841,954,698,721]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">C. saxosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a more rounded horn-like pronotum, with lateral lobes directed sidewards and subquadrate (
<figureCitation box="[874,961,730,754]" captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="35.[192,275,1124,1146]" captionTargetBox="[216,1416,213,1087]" captionTargetId="figure@35.[216,1416,213,1087]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Figure 21. Cota undulata (Cadena-Castañeda and Cardona-Granda, 2015) n. comb., holotype male, left lateral view. Photo by Oscar J. Cadena-Castañeda (CAUD)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3674983" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3674983/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
